    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-09T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-09T07:00:00-05:00" n="157"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/1279: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McClintock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-09T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >February 9, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 9—1:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>226. We are told that the Finnish language broadcast from Moscow<note n="83"
                        xml:id="d157fn83">By the Government-controlled Radio Moscow.</note> last
                    week stated that Helsinki would not be bombed by the Soviet Air Force as the
                    Americans had interceded on the behalf of Finland and were arranging peace
                    between the Soviet Union and this country.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McClintock</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
